    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1943-06-04T11:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1943-06-04T11:00:00-05:00" n="70"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d70">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">125.0046B/6: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Ambassador in the United Kingdom</hi> (<persName
                        type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Winant</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">London</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1943-06-04T18:00:00+02:00"
                            >June 4, 1943—6 p.m.</date>
                        <lb/> [Received June 4—5:32 p.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>3808. Department’s 3220, May 21, 6 p.m. Foreign Office regrets not being able to
                    meet our request for opening a Consulate at Bahrein. Its position and certain
                    suggestions for meeting our needs other than by having consular representation
                    at Bahrein are set forth in considerable detail in an informal communication
                    dated June 2 which is being forwarded by airmail.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Winant</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
